This paper deals with modeling the behavior of agents in multi-agent domains, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also introduces a new technique for predicting and generalizing behavior, which involves principles of maximum entropy and regret, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of decision theory and optimization, which are common topics in robotics (cs.RO).
